title: Add tip to fix "RuntimeError: Broken toolchain"
body_html:
This issue hit me when I tried to install TensorFlow. I checked the "Common Problems" page and when I didn't see this issue there I searched the interwebz to find the fix. Only after I found the fix did I notice the helpful You have not agreed to the Xcode license agreements message further up in the Terminal output...

TESTING

Here's a screenshot of how the updated section of the README looks like in my forked repository:

body:
This issue hit me when I tried to install TensorFlow.  I checked the "Common Problems" page and when I didn't see this issue there I searched the interwebz to find [the fix](http://stackoverflow.com/a/26764577/112705).  Only after I found the fix did I notice the helpful `You have not agreed to the Xcode license agreements` message further up in the Terminal output...

TESTING

Here's a screenshot of how the updated section of the README looks like in [my forked repository](https://github.com/daj/tensorflow/blob/0ea28c550a8d432b09055d5e2288dc3d18dd7c7e/tensorflow/g3doc/get_started/os_setup.md):
